    "recap_headline": "St. John's University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ARLINGTON, TEXAS\n\u2013\u00a0The St. John's baseball team secured its third straight series victory, using a come-from-behind effort to down UT Arlington, 11-7, on Saturday afternoon.\nFacing a five-run deficit after the second inning, the Johnnies (9-12) stormed back to overtake the Mavericks (7-14) in the sixth inning. UTA wouldn't go down quietly, responding with a pair of runs in the seventh.\nThe Red Storm notched a season-high in hits for the second straight game, totaling 17.\nJayder Raifstanger\nled the way for St. John's with four hits.\nJack Tate\nand\nRob Mansour\neach recorded three hits.\nShaun McMillan\n,\nAyden Frey\nand\nLewis Rodriguez\nall registered two hits. Seven Johnnies knocked in a run, with\nJon LeGrande\n, Raifstanger and McMillan all plating a pair. LeGrande swiped a pair of bases in the outting.\nAfter\nEvan Chaffee\nwas pulled in the third inning, the St. John's bullpen provided a boost to help keep the Mavericks at bay. Both\nJack Nestler\nand\nDylan Johnson\nworked out of bases-loaded jams upon entering.\nEvan Hoeckele\nsecured the win with 2.0 innings of scoreless relief.\nUTA came out hot and scored five runs in the first two frames.\nThe Red Storm responded in the top of the third inning. With Mansour and Rodriguez reaching on singles, Raifstanger scored a run on a two-out single. McMillan lifted a routine fly ball to right field, but the fielder lost the ball in the sun and allowed McMillan to reach safely and knock in both runs to make it 5-3.\nSt. John's then scored six unanswered runs to take the lead across the middle innings. In the top of the fifth frame, with Raifstanger and McMillan on second and third with one out, Adam\nAgresti grounded out to the shortstop to score Raifstanger. Tate followed up with an RBI single to knot the contest at 5-5.\nIn the next inning, Raifstanger brought Mansour home from second with a single. The Red Storm then broke the game open in the top of the seventh. With the bases loaded, Rodriguez scored Tate with an RBI single. LeGrande then singled to bring home Mansour and\nDylan Fitzsimmons\n.\nThe Johnnies added two more runs across the eighth and ninth innings to secure the series win.\nSt. John's aims for its second series sweep of the season tomorrow afternoon. First pitch from Clay Gould Ballpark is set for 2 p.m. ET / 1 p.m. CT.",
